The paper deals with optimization problems related to power allocation and user association in multi-cell Massive MIMO downlink systems. This involves the use of advanced techniques such as non-coherent joint transmission, precoding, and max-min fairness. These topics are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control and systems engineering (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and game theory (cs.GT). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
